SIMPLE: feathered
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feathered
<hw>Feath"ered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Clothed, covered, or fitted with (or as with) feathers or wings;
<as>as, a <ex>feathered</ex> animal; a <ex>feathered</ex>
arrow.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rise from the ground like <qex>feathered</qex> Mercury.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nonsense <qex>feathered</qex> with soft and delicate phrases and
pointed with pathetic accent.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. J. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Furnished with anything featherlike; ornamented;
fringed; <as>as, land <ex>feathered</ex> with trees</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a fringe of feathers, as
the legs of certian birds; or of hairs, as the legs of a setter
dog.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Having feathers; -- said of an
arrow, when the feathers are of a tincture different from that of the
shaft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feather-edge</ent>⟦br⟧
